Red Alert 2 Yuri's Revenge VMware Appliance (osx, win7, linux, anything that runs vmware):
http://thepiratebay.org/torrent/5157060

Full game (NOT rip) with working cracks preinstalled, and other goodies:)

So have anyone used this yet - any successful installations? When running the bundle-/setup-script which is supposed to extract the installation files, it reports "magic number does not match".

The file consists of a bash scripts and an attached binary part which is calculated in terms of offset etc. This obviously fails. I am running Debian Lenny btw, and have been well acquainted with Linux since 1992. Maybe I'll look into the script a little better, but I must admit I got a bit sceptical with this error popping up.
